President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed Sunday, September 26, 2021, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day in the United States. This day is designated to honor and pay tribute to the families of fallen service members who have made the ultimate sacrifice in defense of the country's freedom. President Biden expresses his outrage over the recent terrorist attack at the Kabul Airport, which claimed the lives of brave service members who were working to save others. He acknowledges the pain and enduring grief experienced by the families of fallen soldiers and emphasizes the nation's commitment to supporting them. President Biden calls upon government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies as a public expression of gratitude and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.